Description:
LAUNCHING WAP 2.0
CREATE AN INNOVATIVE STATEWIDE WEATHERIZATION ASSISTANCE PROGRAM (WAP): WAP 2.0 WHICH WILL FOCUS ON MULTIFAMILY AFFORDABLE HOUSING (MFAH) PROPERTIES;
• SIGNIFICANTLY INCREASE THE NUMBER OF INCOME-QUALIFIED (IQ) HOUSEHOLDS SERVED BY STATE WAPS BY LEVERAGING ADDITIONAL FUNDING AND RESOURCES WITHOUT INCREASING THE WAP BUDGET;
• DEMONSTRATE HOW TO DEPLOY VERY HIGH EFFICIENCY TECHNOLOGIES (SUCH AS HEAT PUMP HVAC) AND DISTRIBUTED ENERGY RESOURCE (DER) SOLUTIONS IN WAP PROJECTS, INCLUDING SOLAR PV, ENERGY STORAGE, SMART CONTROLS, AND ENERGY MANAGEMENT SYSTEMS;
• COMPLETE DEMONSTRATIONS IN ALIGNMENT WITH DOE DIVERSITY, EQUITY AND INCLUSIVE (DEI) OBJECTIVES AND;
• DISSEMINATE PROJECT FINDINGS TO PROMOTE REPLICATION AND SCALING OF WAP 2.0 FOR MFAH.
• YEAR 1 OBJECTIVE: DEVELOP STRATEGIC ENGAGEMENT PLAN TARGETED TO WAP ADMINISTRATORS, SUBGRANTEES AND STAKEHOLDERS.
• YEAR 2 OBJECTIVE: RECRUIT WAP ADMINISTRATORS IN AT LEAST THREE STATES TO PARTICIPATE IN PILOT PROJECTS.
• YEAR 3 OBJECTIVE: LAUNCH WAP 2.0 WITH AT LEAST ONE WAP ADMINISTRATOR.
